      <body>
         <div xmlns:ecep="http://www.eighteenthcenturypoetry.org/ns"
              type="poem"
              xml:id="tgane-wlt14"
              corresp="#txt_GrayTh1716_lt14"
              subtype="eceptext"
              rendition="#lgvspace">
            <link type="author" target="authors.xml#aut_GrayTh1716"/>
            <head>Imitated [from Buondelmonte]</head>
            <lg>
               <l n="1">Lusit amicitiae interdum velatus amictu,</l>
               <l n="2">    et bene composita veste fefellit Amor.</l>
               <l n="3">Mox irae assumsit cultus, faciemque minantem,</l>
               <l n="4">    inque odium versus, versus et in lacrymas:</l>
               <l n="5">Ludentem fuge, nec lacrymanti, aut crede furenti:</l>
               <l n="6">    idem est dissimili semper in ore Deus.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
